trans-unit.source: Provides a base class that represents contextual details about an individual <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> request.
When implemented in a derived class, initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocketContext"></xref> class.
Gets the anonymous-user identifier for the current <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> connection.
The identifier for the anonymous user.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.HttpApplicationState"></xref> object for the host ASP.NET application.
A reference to the application state.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the root virtual path of the host ASP.NET application.
The path of the application.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Caching.Cache"></xref> object for the current application domain.
The cache object.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the certificate that a remote client issues in response to the server's request for the client's identity.
A string that represents the binary stream of the certificate's content in ASN.1 format.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the number of active WebSocket connections.
The number of active WebSocket connections.

Returns the <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocketContext.Cookies"></xref> collection typed as a <xref href="System.Net.CookieCollection"></xref> for Windows applications that use cookies based on the <xref href="System.Net.Cookie"></xref> class (such as WCF server applications).
The collection of cookies.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the collection of cookies that was sent by a remote client in an <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> message.
The collection of cookies.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the virtual path of the requested file.
As an example of a virtual path, for the URL `http://www.contoso.com/virdir/page.html/tail`, the value of this property is `/virdir/page.html`.
The virtual path.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the collection of headers that was sent by a remote client.
The collection of message headers.
The property is not implemented.
Gets a value that indicates whether a message from a remote client has been authenticated.
`true` if the message has been authenticated; otherwise, `false`.
The property is not implemented.
Gets a value that indicates whether the client is connected to the server.
`true` if the client is connected; otherwise, `false`.
The property is not implemented.
Gets a value that indicates whether the application that hosts the current <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> connection is running in ASP.NET debug mode.
`true` if the application is in debug mode; otherwise, `false`.
The property is not implemented.
Gets a value that indicates whether an <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> message was sent from the local computer.
`true` if the message is from the local computer; otherwise, `false`.
The property is not implemented.
Gets a value that indicates whether the <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> connection uses the WebSocket Secure protocol (WSS).
`true` if the connection uses WSS; otherwise, `false`.
The property is not implemented.

When overridden in a derived class, gets a key/value collection that can be used to share data between a module and a handler during an <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> request.
The key/value collection.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the security token for the current user.
An object that provides identity information to IIS about the current user.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the origin of the WebSocket connection.
The origin of the WebSocket connection.
Gets the virtual path of the requested resource.
As an example of a virtual path, for the URL `http://www.contoso.com/virdir/page.html/tail`, the value of this property is `/virdir/page.html/tail`.
The virtual path.
The property is not implemented.
Gets additional path information for a resource that has a URL extension.
As an example of a virtual path, for the URL `http://www.contoso.com/virdir/page.html/tail`, the value of this property is `/tail`.
A string that contains additional path information for a resource.
The property is not implemented.
Gets an object that contains user profile data.
A <xref href="System.Web.Profile.ProfileBase"></xref> object if the application configuration file contains a definition for the profile's properties; otherwise, `null`.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the collection of query string variables from an <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> message that was sent by the client.
The collection of query string variables that was sent by the client.
For example, if the request URL is http://www.contoso.com/default.aspx?id=44, this property returns a collection that contains a single item whose value is id=44.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the portion of a URL that follows the website name in an <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> message that was sent by the client.
The part of the URL that follows the website name.
For example, if the complete request URL is http://www.contoso.com/default.aspx?id=44, the value of this property is /default.aspx?id=44.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the original Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) of an <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> message that was sent by the client.
The original URI.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the encrypted key that is sent in the handshake request to establish an <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> connection.
The encrypted key.
The property is not implemented.
Gets a list of application-level protocols (subprotocols) that a client can use to send messages using an <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> connection.
The list of subprotocols, separated by spaces.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the version of the WebSocket protocol that an <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> connection must use.
The specified version of the WebSocket protocol.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.HttpServerUtility"></xref> object that provides methods that are used in processing requests.
The <xref href="System.Web.HttpServerUtility"></xref> object that provides methods that are used in processing requests.
Gets a name/value collection of variables that provide information about the web server and about the current <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> connection.
The collection of server variables.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the timestamp of an <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> message that was sent by the client.
The timestamp.
The property is not implemented.
Gets unvalidated versions of one or more field values that are submitted in an <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> message.
An unvalidated value has not been checked by ASP.NET request validation and might contain markup, script, or reserved characters.
For more information about request validation, see <xref:System.Web.UnvalidatedRequestValues>.
The unvalidated values.
The property is not implemented.
Gets a collection of URI data about the message that was sent by the client prior to the current message.
The URI data.
The property is not implemented.
Gets an object that represents the security context of the user for the current <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> connection.
The security context of the user.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the name of the remote client.
The browser name and version.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the IP address of the remote client.
The IP address.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the DNS name of the remote client.
The DNS name.
The property is not implemented.
Gets the collection of language preferences for the remote client.
The client language preferences.
The property is not implemented.
Gets a reference to the current <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> instance.
The current <xref href="System.Web.WebSockets.AspNetWebSocket"></xref> instance.
The property is not implemented.
